From shell, inside `/code_MC` directory:

- N.B. When executing the simulation, I incurred in the error:

	*** stack smashing detected ***: terminated
	Aborted (core dumped)

  A `make clean` fixed it. It would be a good idea to give a `make clean`
  anyway, just in case!
- To compile: `make`.

From shell, inside _this_ directory:
- To run the first program: `./ex1.sh`;
- To run the second program: `./ex2.sh`;

From shell, inside `/code_MD` directory:
- To compile: `make`;

From shell, inside _this_ directory:
- To run the third program: `./ex3.sh`.

There's no need of changing the input files or creating new directories: 
the scripts provided should take care of everything. The scripts set also 
the values of the input file. To change the input values the best option 
could be to modify the scripts themselves. The programs are independent. 
